ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When it's hard to get your PrEP prescription
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When you've been drinking
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When you've been using drugs
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When your partner(s) is upset by you taking PrEP
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When you think PrEP has side effects
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When taking PrEP feels like a lot of trouble
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When you worry your partner(s) thinks you sleep around because you use PrEP
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When you think your risk for getting HIV is very low
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you that you could continue to take PrEP?: When you use other preventive measures like condoms
Notes: 1 = Very unconfident; 2 = Somewhat unconfident; 3 = Neutral (neither confident nor unconfident); 4 = Confident; 5 = Very Confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When HIV preventive drugs cannot be obtained immediately
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When you are (recently) drinking or using other drugs
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When your partner is upset with it
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When you feel it has side effects
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When the trouble of HIV is too much
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When you think that your partners will be angry with the use of HIV preventive drugs
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When you think the risk of AIDS is very low
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident

ElementDescription: In the following situations, how confident are you to continue to use HIV preventive medicine?: When you have used other protective measures such as condoms
Notes: 1 = Strongly unconfident; 2 = Unconfident; 3 = Comparatively confident; 4 = Confident; 5 = Strongly confident
